President Joe Biden, along with his senior advisors, held a virtual event with CEOs and senior leaders from industries affected by the semiconductor shortage. This shortage is currently impacting American workers and families, making it a top priority for the President. During the event, industry leaders discussed short and long-term approaches to address the chip shortage. They emphasized the need for transparency in the semiconductor supply chain to mitigate current shortages and improve demand forecasting to address future challenges. Additionally, there was a focus on encouraging more semiconductor manufacturing capacity in the United States to prevent future shortages. The event also highlighted how President Biden's infrastructure investments in the American Jobs Plan will strengthen America's competitiveness and national security by building the infrastructure of the future and enhancing supply chain resilience. This will ensure that the United States remains a global leader in critical technologies and the transition to a clean energy future.